        <p>నేను honestly చెప్తాను: complex liver cases లో, dedicated hepatobiliary surgery program ఉన్న centres better equipped ఉంటాయి. CION Tumor Board లో hepatobiliary expertise ఉంది.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="en-block">
        <p>Liver cancer surgery covers two main types: primary liver cancer (HCC) and metastatic liver disease, most commonly from colorectal cancer.</p>
        <p>For HCC, liver function (Child-Pugh score) and tumour characteristics determine candidacy. Barcelona Clinic Liver Cancer (BCLC) staging guides surgery indications. Adequate future liver remnant (FLR) is critical for surgical safety.</p>
        <p>For colorectal liver metastases, surgery can offer long-term survival. Study data shows 5-year survival of 30-50% is possible in resected colorectal liver metastasis patients. Combination with systemic chemotherapy often gives better outcomes.</p>
        <p>I will be honest: for complex liver cases, centres with dedicated hepatobiliary surgery programs are better equipped. The CION Tumor Board has hepatobiliary expertise.</p>
